BUSINESS RISK MANAGEMENT ANALYST (ABU DHABI-BASED)DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES:Provides consulting services on Business Risk Management across the company. Promotes awareness of Business Risk Management (BRM) and facilitates workshops and the application of BRM techniques across all business activities and to all levels within company.Consults and facilitates ad-hoc risk analysis projects and other selected strategic activities as required by senior management.MINIMUM REQUIREMENTSEDUCATIONBachelor Degree in Business Administration or equivalent. Preferably a relevant professional qualification in BRM/ERMEXPERIENCE5-6 years experience at least of which 3 were auditing or risk management preferably within oil and gas industry.Ability to think strategically with a high level of understanding business process. Excellent presentation and communication skills.Proficient in English LanguageUp to 50 years oldNOTE: Please submit your CV in word format kindly make sure to indicate your date of birth and Nationality.Cv's without the required information will be disregarded.
